Notes: Taxonomy: Scientific name quandry! Lolium multiflorum deprecated: https://www.calflora.org/cgi-bin/species_query.cgi?where-taxon=Festuca+perennis
Notes: Environmental Tolerances: Does very poorly under low-N conditions like most grasses.
Soil Drainage: ["Poorly drained","Somewhat poorly drained","Moderately well drained","Well drained","Saturated muck","Well drained muck"]
Notes: Termination [Goal: Method: Timing: Herbicide resistance has been documented in annual ryegrass. If using tillage, multiple passes may be necessary. Mow to 6" height to improve likelihood of winter survival.
Notes: Weeds: If mowing, leave 3-4" to ensure regrowth;  Must be killed before it joints or after heading
